480":"1480","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Great Leighs, Essex, England":"Great Leighs, Essex, England","Bailey Flat Farm, Buxton, Peak district, Derbyshire, England":"Buxton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England":"Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England","Ovenden, Yorkshire, England":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Crowther","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly Yorkshire): variant of   Crowder   1.","Scottish: possibly a variant of <b>McGrouther</b>, from Gaelic <b>Mac Grùdair</b> ‘son of (the) brewer’, from <i>grùdair</i> ‘brewer’."],"variants":[{"name":"Crowder","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>crouder</i>, <i>crouther</i> ‘player of the croud’, a stringed instrument sometimes known as the Welsh fiddle (Middle English <i>croud</i>, a borrowing of Welsh <i>crwth</i>). In Wales and in English counties bordering Wales the name may have been an Anglicized form of the equivalent Welsh <i>crythor</i> ‘fiddler’. The surname also occurs as   Crowther  .","Americanized form of German   Krauter   or its Dutch cognates <b>Kruiter</b> and <b>Kruider</b>."]},{"name":"Crowthers","meanings":["English (Northumberland): variant of   Crowther  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Crowther was born in 1480, in Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England as the daughter of Mr. Crowther. She married John Mawde le Bailly in 1495, in Buxton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1534, in Great Leighs, Essex, England, at the age of 54."},"et":{"1480–1534":"1480–1534","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1502–1550":"1502–1550","1385–Male":"1385–Surnud","1502":"1502","1534":"1534","1 January 1502":"1. jaanuar 1502","1532":"1532","1477":"1477","1495":"1495","1385":"1385","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Great Leighs, Essex, England":"Great Leighs, Essex, England","Bailey Flat Farm, Buxton, Peak district, Derbyshire, England":"Buxton, Derbyshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England":"Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England","Ovenden, Yorkshire, England":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1480–1534":"1480–1534","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1502–1550":"1502–1550","1385–Male":"1385–Kuollut","1502":"1502","1534":"1534","1 January 1502":"1. tammikuuta 1502","1532":"1532","1477":"1477","1495":"1495","1385":"1385","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Great Leighs, Essex, England":"Great Leighs, Essex, England","Bailey Flat Farm, Buxton, Peak district, Derbyshire, England":"Buxton, Derbyshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England":"Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England","Ovenden, Yorkshire, England":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1480–1534":"1480–1534","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1502–1550":"1502–1550","1385–Male":"1385–Décédé","1502":"1502","1534":"1534","1 January 1502":"1 janvier 1502","1532":"1532","1477":"1477","1495":"1495","1385":"1385","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Great Leighs, Essex, England":"Great Leighs, Essex, Angleterre","Bailey Flat Farm, Buxton, Peak district, Derbyshire, England":"Buxton, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England":"Heptonstall, Everwyck, Angleterre","Ovenden, Yorkshire, England":"Ovenden, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Crowther est née en 1480, à Heptonstall, Everwyck, Angleterre, fille de Mr. Crowther. Elle a épousé John Mawde le Bailly en 1495, à Buxton, Derbyshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1534, à Great Leighs, Essex, Angleterre, à l’âge de 54 ans."},"de":{"1480–1534":"1480–1534","1477–1532":"1477–1532","1502–1550":"1502–1550","1385–Male":"1385–Verstorben","1502":"1502","1534":"1534","1 January 1502":"1. Januar 1502","1532":"1532","1477":"1477","1495":"1495","1385":"1385","1550":"1550","1480":"1480","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Great Leighs, Essex, England":"Great Leighs, Essex, England","Bailey Flat Farm, Buxton, Peak district, Derbyshire, England":"Buxton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom","Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England":"Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England","Ovenden, Yorkshire, England":"Ovenden, Yorkshire, England","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Crowther wurde 1480 in Heptonstall, Yorkshire, England, als Tochter von Mr. Crowther geboren. Sie hat 1495 in Buxton, Derbyshire, England, United Kingdom John Mawde le Bailly geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1534 im Alter von 54 Jahren in Great Leighs, Essex, England."},"ht":{"1480–1534":"1480–1534","1477–1532":"1477–1532